#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: actors-cluster-discovery
description: Actor v1.6.x — joinCluster seed-list gossip in single-node mode
---

# Cluster discovery — joinCluster

`joinCluster(seeds)` connects to a list of seed nodes and, once connected,
exchanges peer lists so the whole cluster is reachable without N² manual
`connectNode` calls.  This test exercises single-node behaviour: an empty
seed list succeeds silently and leaves the runtime in join-mode; actors work
normally after the call.

```scalascript
runActors {
  joinCluster(List())

  val worker = spawn { () =>
    receive {
      case "ping" => println("pong")
    }
  }
  worker ! "ping"
}
```
